parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the radiator can cause coolant to leak into the transmission, leading to damage to the transmission and potentially causing the vehicle to stall or become inoperable, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle may hesitate to move
or stall when accelerating; the transmission may slip or fail to engage; the radiator fluid may leak into the transmission
causing a milky or tanish-colored liquid to appear; the vehicle may overheat; and the check engine light may illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel gauge can cause drivers to run out of fuel, leading to accidents or leaving them stranded, which can be a safety hazard.
symptoms: The fuel gauge displays incorrect readings
shows empty when the tank is full
or shows full when the tank is empty
the service engine light comes on
the fuel gauge drops suddenly to empty
the fuel gauge does not register a correct reading of fuel in the tank.
